'''predatory'''

===Adjective===

# To [[prey]] on other [[living]] [[entities]], for [[food]], or to [[preserve]] or [[guard]] ones own [[territory]]. 
# To prey on, or [[exploit]], others for ones own personal [[gain]].
 

: ''See also: [[pedator]]


===Noun===

# predatory pricing: when [[companies]] [[price]] [[goods]] or [[services]] at [[prices]] that [[hurt]] [[their]] [[competition|competitors]], and gain [[market share]] for [[themselves]], often to [[force]] the [[competition]] to act in a [[desired]] [[manner]], and to the [[detriment]] to their own [[profits]].